column3: “Yo I was vibrating and shit”

“So they had this on sale at Lake Effect so I couldn't say no to trying this bud out

-Look: Even though it had the standard green bud with orange hairs, it has them in a proportion that has them looking somewhat reminiscent of orange colored citrus

-Smell:  It has a very well rounded bouquet; you have the rich pungent notes of a good strain along with a refreshing and obvious citrus note

-Taste: This has hints of a...”

“What's so damn lovely about Tangerine Dream is its somewhat unique fusion of relaxation and stimulation. Smoking this strain for the first time, I felt like a triumphant alchemist who'd finally found the real 'philosopher's stone', cerebral, rational, and penetrative. 

The moment you inhale this bud, its indica side melts away all mental tension, untangling emotions and thoughts, enveloping the user in a sense of sa...”
“One of my favorite strains! Smells amazing, smokes awesome and tastes like it smells! Good head buzz but still functional!”

“This is a great strain. Tangerine Dream is like being wrapped in the warm embrace of Morpheus. The body is significant enough to relax and relieve stress and fatigue. The head high is slightly overpowering making this hybrid more suitable for activities. Unless you burn down the pipe so to speak. Then it will meld you to the couch. Overall I like this strain it's very pleasant.”

“This was the most insane tasting bud I've ever had, it literally tasted like someone rolled a joint with orange peels, it was so tangeriney. It was a really smooth, refreshing smoke but it left behind a pretty drastic dry mouth. Definitely worth it though, as the high was bright and clear and left you feeling energised.”
“Great daytime med for anxiety or depression. Keeps me active and attentive but still with a slight buffer of calmness. Not heady.”
“Tangerine Dream is a very clear headed high, that can help block pain and reduce stress.  Very citrusy smell, pretty smooth, slightly acidic taste on the exhale.”
“This strain makes me think of Blue Dream in effect, giving you the mellow body with mild indica and a wonderful connected cerebral intensity that allows great focus throughout the day.”

“Tangerine Dream is one of those really nice energetic focused highs but still keeps you grounded, so there is no paranoia.  Real relaxing and mellow at the same time.  I think the best thing about this bud though is the smell and the taste.  Sweet, but not overly sugary.  If you are drinking a soda when you smoke it, it takes on the sugary taste - tasty!!.  One of my fav's.”
“Tastes delicious!! Definitely helps with depression and anxiety!”

“I've seen this strain in shops, but until now, I hadn't purchased any for whatever reason. After doing some research, I purchased an eighth of Tangerine Dream, because I'm always looking to cycle my meds so I'm receiving the most benefit from their use. I used TD for about a week during which time I utilized it as my wake and bake sativa strain. I've found that with cannibus I may treat my conditions and there are se...”

“Migraine pain 6; nausea 5-6 when I medicated round 1630 or so. Takes bout 5 min to start working. Pain/nausea gone. Head high strong but also energetic. Was able to cook my hubby a healthy dinner & do a load of laundry. Body high perfect. Still very stoned & body high is just startin to wear off @ 2000. Lasts a while which is very nice. Highly recommend for daytime use. Might keep ya up if ya use to late in the day. ...”

“I LOVE tangerine dream! Although having recently had surgery and noticing that this strain was very good for managing the pain, I want to emphasize this strain for people who have pain and stress, but can't handle all medical mj due to anxiety. Some strains cause an anxious reaction in me, but tangerine dream is not one of them. I can smoke, manage my pain, relax and not have an issue. I love it; perfect medicine.”

“WOW! 10AM, Amsterdam on a cold October morning... strolling into Barney's on our first stop over a long weekend of dutch hospitality" :) the budvendor highly recommended "Tangerine Dream" to get us started for the day and who would have thought the first strand I buy in the notorious 'dam be this good! Totally blew my socks off and one of my most memorable smokes... EVER (and that's saying a lot because the truth is...”"

“Based on a two-week cure, will update after 4+ wk

Taste:  certainly citrus/tangerine-ish on the tongue.  At 2-weeks cure I only enjoy this one in joint form (zig zag orange).  In a glass piece it's still super-harsh.

Aroma:  not too strong until... you bust open a flower, then I get a big hit of Haze (I've got some G13xHaze and it compares), with deep citrus undertones .  
The jar started to emit pleasant aromas af...”

“Very nice head high if you smoke a little, or couch lock like a mother if you smoke a little more. Know your limits on that boundry with this strain as its pretty easy to cross into the couch lock area. Good for a morning smoke with a cuppa joe. Definitely recommend”

“I've been trying so many different strains lately.  I know, rough life.  This Tangerine Dream is the BEST I've tasted in recent memory.  The taste is outstanding and the effect is instant.  It only takes a small amount.  It's especially good for my fibromyalgia.”
“This strain caught me off guard! It's a very uplifting and euphoric high. And goddayum is it tasty. One of my all time favorites.”

“Smells almost exactly like a tangerine. My stuff wasn't dry so a fat bowl lasted about 6 hits. This stuff got me high enough that after 3 hits I put the pipe down, and spaced out for like 15mins until I realized I still had part of a bowl... That's how I know it's good stuff.”
“One of the best stains I've tried. It gave me a chill head high, while taking away my back pain at the same time. My body felt great for a few hours. Would recommend this to first timers.”

“Feels very medicinal so probably < or =20% THC & >.5% CBD
Definitely citrus on the tongue with a light and clear head buzz thus validating itself as the working man's weed. Seems like an all purpose strain as it relaxes the muscles & or any anxiety as well any stiffness in the body. I believe this G13/S5 Hybrid to be 2 parts Indica with 1 part Sativa. A professional grade bud for that special spot in any avid medicin...”

“Well this strain definitely lives up to the reviews and description. I've had a mastectomy in September and just finished a few weeks of radiation and I've been really sore. So Lately I've been leaning towards indicas and indica hybrids for there pain profiles but I've got to say, this has knocked out most of my pain. Very euphoric, and uplifting, my head is clear and focused yet my muscles are relaxed. Beautiful str...”

“This strain is very interesting that the fact it distinctively smells like Tangerines and tastes earthy and a hint of sweetness. Its perfect for a good ease-out end of the day and just to sit and smoke either or alone or with friends its all good due to the high being dependant on how your mood is while smoking. These buds have very dark leaves and looks almost as if the THC and the brown hairs are mixing into brown ...”

For a novice smoker i suspect it packs a punch (couch-lock) but for seasoned smokers it's probably more of an everyday medicinal pre-post work or work-out, socializing, relaxing &/or any creative pursuits, pick me up. Smokin...”
“love this powerfull sativa strain ❤️ i'm so fly so high... 🍁🔥😄”

“Very interesting strain, but in a good way. It actually smells really fruity, and tastes earthy with a hint of citrus. Great head high too, something you could just sit back and smoke all day. Definitely recommend.”

“The most dekicious citrus and akmost viniilla undertones - just a pleasure to inhale letting vapor roll over the palet.  Immediate relief of my joint pains while still being functional.  A must try !   As always, purchased from Thrive Market in North Las Vegas - best quality and service in the valley guaranteed !”

“Wow! Tangerine dream is a cannon of happy pellets. Alternatives has this strain down. I don't know who brings this stuff in but they know how to do it. A cross between old AK-47 and Sour-Diesel, this ganja puts the Pow in Power and leaves you with the errrr... A tangy sweet aftertaste, a soft but euphoric body high, and a smooth smoking texture, this strain is now on my top 5 favorites list.”

Second, the thing that impressed me the most was that it actually smelled just like a fresh tangerine! EXACTLY like a fresh tangerine! I have never ...”

This hits quick .. and you for sure get the point quick;y ..this will be your last hit.  The giggles are uncontrollable and you laugh at basically nothing ..   everything moves very slow .. and I found myself repeating a lot of stuff.  Re...”
“High quality flower. Superior taste, hits smooth and the high took me to the moon. One of my favorite all around strains. They always have it at Life's  RX" Renton East Highlands.”"

unless white widow or ak-47 are in stock

Positive effects: While I didn’t have any pain, I felt happy, slightly energetic & relaxed. No sense of paranoia.
